org.sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM issues INNER JOIN projects ON projects.id = issues.project_id INNER JOIN issue_statuses ON issue_statuses.id = issues.status_id WHERE projects.status <> 9 AND (SELECT 1 AS one FROM enabled_modules AS em WHERE em.project_id = projects.id AND em.name = 'issue_tracking') IS NOT NULL AND issues.project_id IN (SELECT projects.id FROM projects LEFT OUTER JOIN custom_values ON custom_values.customized_type = 'Project' AND custom_values.customized_id = projects.id AND custom_values.custom_field_id = 112 WHERE custom_values.value IN ('Foo') AND 1 = 1)
